# Project Overview

Cyber Shield – Spot the Phishing Scam is an educational browser-based game designed to teach children aged 10–12 how to identify phishing scams and stay safe online. The game uses interactive missions, rewards, explanations, and cyber safety tips to create an engaging learning experience.

The project focuses on:

* phishing awareness
* cybersecurity education
* accessibility
* child-friendly design
* responsive web development
* interactive learning

---

# Target Audience

Children aged 10–12 years old.

The game interface and gameplay were designed to:

* use simple language
* provide large readable text
* include bright child-friendly colors
* support accessibility
* encourage safe online behaviour

---

# Development Goals

The main goals of the project were:

1. Create an educational cybersecurity game
2. Teach phishing awareness interactively
3. Build a responsive browser-based application
4. Apply accessibility and UX principles
5. Create coursework-ready documentation and GitHub evidence
6. Improve teamwork and development workflow skills

